title_result: 76-year-old Oneida Indian Nation Member Sets 10 New Weightlifting World Records at AAU Powerlifting World Championships;Weightlifter Ray Fougnier recently set multiple world records at the 2019 Amateur Athletic Union Powerlifting World Championships, continuing to win medals and stun audience members. At age 76, the Oneida Indian Nation member delivered his best effort to date- achieving ten new records and winning the event's Best Lifter Award.
